description.narrative: During 2016, UNICEF support to the Ministry of Health focused on the implementation of the new Mother and Child Health (MCH) regulatory framework, by producing a budgetary cost estimation tool; training health care personnel on the MCH standards and data collection; and strengthening legislation on Breast Milk Substitutes (BMS) marketing. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:08/01/2017

title.narrative: % use of child growth monitoring charts during mother and child visits to health centres (in areas targeted for introduction of this new tool)

baseline.value: Child growth is not monitored systematically

target.value: 2014:100% of MCH preventive care centres monitor child growth and provide counselling to parents (in target areas)

actual.value: 2016:Indicator not relevant beyond the MDG-F project completed in 2014

title.narrative: % of families that have access to quality maternal, neonatal and child health services, including patronage (in target areas)

target.value: 2016:100% (in target areas implementing the new MCH care standard)

actual.value: 2016:Indicator fully met in the target area of Durres, where new MCH framework was implemented in 2016

title.narrative: equity targets for children are included in the national health strategy

actual.value: 2016:Partially included. The national core List and Manual of Health Indicators (adopted in 2016) include child-specific indicators. The List is aligned with the contents of the newly adopted Strategy and Action plan for Reproductive Health 2017-2021, Non-Communicable Diseases National Programme 2016-202

title.narrative: enforcement mechanisms are in place to support scaling up of system changes in MCH preventive services based on recently approved MCH regulatory framework

baseline.value: enforcement and accountability/performance monitoring mechanism not in place

target.value: 2016:key elements of the enforcement mechanism and performance monitoring are established

actual.value: 2016:Key elements of the mechanism (training modules, monitoring instruments, costing estimate tool) are developed and tested in the target region of Durres.
